Medusa
Speedy parallel network login brute-forcer

Password Attacks
Description
Medusa is a speedy, parallel, and modular login brute-forcer. It supports many protocols including HTTP, FTP, SSH, SMB, MySQL, and more.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which medusa
Install command:

sudo apt install medusa
Basic Syntax
medusa -h <host> -u <user> -P <wordlist> -M <module>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
medusa -h 192.168.1.1 -u admin -P wordlist.txt -M ssh

SSH brute force	Crack SSH login	
medusa -h 192.168.1.1 -U users.txt -P pass.txt -M ftp

FTP brute force	Crack FTP login	
medusa -h 192.168.1.1 -u admin -P wordlist.txt -M mysql

MySQL brute force	Crack MySQL login	
medusa -h 192.168.1.1 -u admin -P wordlist.txt -M http -m DIR:/admin

HTTP basic auth	Web login brute force	
medusa -H hosts.txt -U users.txt -P pass.txt -M smb

SMB multi-host	Network-wide brute force	
medusa -d

List modules	See supported protocols	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Choose target and protocol
2
Prepare username and password lists
3
Select module with -M
4
Run medusa
5
Review cracked credentials
Understanding the Output
Shows login attempts and successful credentials with [SUCCESS] marker.

Important Warnings
•
Brute forcing is illegal without permission
•
Can lock out accounts
•
Use rate limiting to avoid detection
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
